.TH "stopMaintenanceMode" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
stopMaintenanceMode \- stop data center maintenance mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]dc.stopMaintenanceMode([options])\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDC
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used for disaster recovery.
It stops the Maintenance mode of the cluster and restores normal operating
state.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
options ( \f[I]object, optional\f[] )
.PP
Through the options parameter, you can specify the parameters for Maintenance
mode:
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName ( \f[I]string\f[] ): The hostname where Maintenance mode stops taking
effect (mutually exclusive with Location)
.RS 2
.PP
The specified hostname must exist in the current cluster.
All nodes on this host will stop Maintenance mode.
.PP
Format: \f[C]HostName: "sdbserver"\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Location ( \f[I]string\f[] ): The location set where Maintenance mode stops
taking effect (mutually exclusive with HostName)
.RS 2
.PP
The specified location set must exist in the current cluster.
All replication group nodes in this location set will stop Maintenance mode.
.PP
Format: \f[C]Location: "GuangZhou"\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Domain ( \f[I]string | string array\f[] ): Filter by domain, only operate on
data groups belonging to the specified domain(s).
A single domain name or an array of domain names can be specified
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]Domain: "mydomain"\f[] or
\f[C]Domain: ["domain1", "domain2"]\f[]
.RE
